user.about: Hi, my name is Marius, I was born in Lithuania.I moved to Ireland 14 years ago and I live in Cootehill, County Cavan. I absolutely love photography It has brought so much joy and passion to my life since I got my first digital camera. Photography has brought me close to nature. Even the smallest things in nature are so beautiful and unique. Thank you for taking an interest in my photography. I hope you enjoy viewing as much as I enjoy shooting.

Es gibt nichts schöneres...einfach los laufen..natur...Rucksack voll mit Equipment...der Hund glücklich 10 m. voraus...die Bäche rauschen...Nebel zieht auf...bergauf noch 4 km...prächtig erheben sich die schneebedeckten Berge vor gleissendem Licht...ich bin Landschafts-Fotograf...es gibt nichts schöneres...komm Boomi...:-)

INSTAGRAM @JULIAWIMMERLIN. Ukrainian-born currently Swiss-based commercial and travel photographer (prints https://www.artofokus.com/en/57_julia-wimmerlin). My specialty is... diversity! I love photography as a whole and will always bring something personal whether it's a portrait or a travel shot. My strength is my creative approach combined with true emotions. 

I love photography and I love sharing my love for it with others that's why I teach photography at Swiss Photo Club. I'm  a 500px Ambassador (as you can see at the top of the page:) I'm also a contributor to National Geographic Your Shot - National Geographic's photography community. I hold a number of international photography awards including the latest shortlist of my mother- baby orangutans photo "Connection" in the "Natural World and Wildlife" category, Open competition of Sony World Photography Awards 2020 (UK).

photos.name: Magic water circle
photos.description: This magical place in the highlands of Iceland represents Iceland in a perfect manner. Black lave mountain, green moose and a colourful small river. I was lucky that the sun came out for a few seconds when i did discover this place. A bit more work in post processing as the contrast are very hight in such moments in such a landscape. I thought for a few seconds to include a bit more of the lava stones into the foreground. But after my first step forward i decided that this would be too dangerous. Beautiful but difficult location.

photos.description: It is a mountain of volcanic origin. It did not stop raining in the 2 days I was there: wind and rain incessantly. No dejó de llover en los 2 días que estuve allí: viento y lluvia sin cesar. Así que me olvidé de trípode y filtros, caminé y disfruté lo que pude del lugar.
